Class GraphicsProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • fingerprint_recognition.GraphicsProcessor

  • public class GraphicsProcessor
extends java.lang.Object

      • processBatch

        public java.util.List<Data> processBatch(java.lang.String sourcePath,
                                         java.lang.String destinationPath,
                                         int startingIndex,
                                         int imageCount,
                                         int windowWidth,
                                         int windowHeight,
                                         int overlapFactor)
        Processes images in a specified folder - extract minutiae, use them to generate data set for tne neural network and generate processed images with marked minutiae.
        Parameters:
        sourcePath - Path to folder containing source images.
        destinationPath - Path to folder into which processed images will be written.
        startingIndex - Index (name) of the first image.
        imageCount - Number of images in the folder.
        windowWidth - Width of the processing window.
        windowHeight - Height of the processing window.
        Returns:
        Processed minutiae vector to be used as input to the neural network.
